The National Working Committee, NWC, of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, on behalf of the National Executive Committee, NEC, has reconstituted the Kaduna State Caretaker Committee to pilot the affairs of the party in the state. Kola Ologbondiyan, National Publicity Secretary of the party, said the action of the NWC, which is pursuant to section 29(2)(b) and 31(2) (e) of the PDP Constitution (2017 as amended), is consequent upon the expiration of the tenure of the outgoing state caretaker committee. The statement explained that the reconstituted Caretaker Committee is charged with the sole responsibility of running the affairs of the party in Kaduna state until a new executive committee is elected, for a period not exceeding 90 days (3 months). The statement added that the members of the reconstituted Kaduna State Caretaker Committee would have Barr. Bashir Tanimu Dutsen-Ma as the Chairman. Others are Hon. Ashiru Abdullahi K, Dr. Abdu Rahama Usman, Ahmed Abdu Zaria, Hon. Lawal Balarabe and Jerry G. Ishaya. The rest are Imam Lawal Adamu, Edward Masha, John Ayuba, Hon. Maria Dogo and Hon. Abdullahi Ali Kano as Secretary of the Committee.